1.pow(x,n)
if n <0, return 1/pow(x,-n)
recursion - if n is odd x*pow(x,n-1), if n is even pow(x,n/2)*pow(x,n/2)
iteration - Example pow(3, 15)
pow(3, 15) = 3*pow(3, 14) = 3*pow(9, 7) = 3*9*pow(9, 6) = 3*9*pow(81, 3) = 3*9*81*pow(81,2) = 3*9*81*6541
If n is odd, multiply ans with x and make n to n-1; if n is even, change x to x*x
time complexity - log(n)

